</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[831,1436,258,313]" pageId="12" pageNumber="87">
most elytral punctures are in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lobl" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[1173,1303,258,281]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[1173,1303,258,281]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="87">B. punctata</emphasis>
